Developer Support Policy

Effective Date: 29 June 2026

This Support Policy outlines the assistance available to our users and how to contact us.

Our Commitment

We strive to provide a high-quality experience by:

* Maintaining compatibility with supported versions of iOS, iPadOS, macOS, watchOS and tvOS.
* Addressing bugs and performance issues through regular updates.
* Responding to support requests in a timely and professional manner.
* Continuously improving features based on user feedback.

Support Services

We can assist with:

* Installing and setting up the app.
* Account and subscription enquiries.
* Restoring purchases.
* Questions about app features and functionality.
* Reporting bugs or unexpected behaviour.
* Suggestions for improvements and new features.

Response Times

Our goal is to respond to support enquiries within:

* General enquiries: 2–5 business days
* Technical issues: 2–5 business days
* Critical issues affecting app functionality: As soon as reasonably possible

Response times may vary during public holidays or periods of high demand.

Before Contacting Support

To help us resolve your issue quickly, please include:

* Your device model.
* Operating system version.
* App name and version.
* A description of the issue.
* Steps to reproduce the problem.
* Screenshots or screen recordings, if applicable.

Please do not send passwords, payment details, or other sensitive personal information.

In-App Purchases and Subscriptions

Purchases and subscriptions are processed securely by Apple through the App Store.

For billing issues, refunds, or payment enquiries, please contact Apple Support directly, as developers cannot access payment information or issue App Store refunds.

We are happy to assist with restoring purchases or troubleshooting subscription access within the app.

Feature Requests

We welcome ideas that help improve apps. While we cannot guarantee every suggestion will be implemented, all feedback is reviewed and considered during future development.

Software Updates

Apps are actively maintained. Updates may include:

* Bug fixes
* Performance improvements
* New features
* Compatibility updates
* Improvements to astronomical and environmental data

We recommend keeping automatic updates enabled to ensure the best experience.

Service Availability

While we aim to provide uninterrupted service, some features rely on third-party services such as weather providers, mapping services, or Apple platform services. Temporary interruptions may occur due to maintenance or circumstances beyond our control.

